summary: This is a 2021 email chain between federal prosecutors and FBI agents discussing the retrieval of notes and documents from 2006 FBI interviews related to the Epstein investigation. The emails reference interviews of witnesses from August 2006 and the need to locate agent notes and documents provided by a witness.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: FBI Special Agent from the New York Field Office, Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking unit, who is being asked to provide notes from a 2006 interview.

persons.name: Assistant United States Attorney
persons.context: Assistant United States Attorney from the Southern District of New York who is requesting notes and documents from 2006 FBI interviews for a grand jury proceeding.

connections.description: Prosecutor requesting investigative materials (interview notes and documents) from an FBI agent for a legal proceeding.

events.title: FBI Interview of Witness
events.description: An FBI interview was conducted with a witness (referred to by initials in the email). The witness provided a copy of hours worked at Epstein's residence and personal notes from her time of employment.

events.title: FBI Interview of Witness WM
events.description: An FBI interview was conducted with a witness identified as WM. The prosecutor is requesting the agent's notes from this interview.

locations: United States Attorney's Office, Southern District of New York
keyFacts: The document is a 2021 email chain showing prosecutors actively seeking 2006 FBI interview notes and documents for a grand jury proceeding related to Epstein.
It references a specific witness interview from August 22, 2006, where the witness provided documentation of hours worked at Epstein's residence and personal notes.
It references another witness interview from August 15, 2006, with an individual identified as 'WM'.
The emails indicate that the requested agent notes from these 2006 interviews were not readily available in the initial document production, prompting a search.
